---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SaaS Pricing Use Cases | PricingNest"
  description="Practical flows for SaaS pricing decisions: usage-based pricing, API pricing, infra cost recovery, unit economics, and pricing experiments."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>SaaS pricing use cases</h1>
    <p>
      These short guides chain calculators into repeatable workflows. Use them to model a pricing change, sanity-check unit
      economics, or back into prices from cost drivers.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/saas-pricing/">Browse all tools</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Start with unit pricing</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <section class="card col8">
      <h2>Use cases</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        This hub is meant to help teams choose the right calculator path quickly. Start here when you know the category
        of decision you are making, then move into the calculator and the strongest retained guide for deeper evaluation.
      </p>
      <ol class="list">
        <li>
          <a href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/usage-based-pricing/">Usage-based pricing</a> — set a per-unit price from costs,
          overhead, and target margin.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/api-pricing/">API pricing</a> — turn call volume and unit costs into a monthly plan
          price and implied rate.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/infra-cost-recovery/">Infra cost recovery</a> — price bandwidth and storage-heavy
          features with predictable margins.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/unit-economics/">SaaS unit economics</a> — connect MRR/ARR, churn, LTV, CAC payback,
          and break-even CAC.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/saas-pricing/use-cases/pricing-experiments/">Pricing experiments</a> — model price increases and annual
          discount tradeoffs.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">How to use these</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Start with the calculator closest to the decision you need to defend internally.</li>
        <li>Use share links and CSV export to align on assumptions before debating packaging or discount policy.</li>
        <li>Open a retained guide when you need decision criteria, trade-offs, or implementation notes.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Start points</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Price per unit calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/api-pricing-calculator/">API cost calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/storage-cost-calculator/">Cost per GB calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/compute-cost-estimator/">Compute pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/annual-discount-calculator/">Annual discount calculator</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Related hubs</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/">Toolkit</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/">Guides</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/">Glossary</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
